<br>
Golden Eftreeti Boots                        <br>
<br>
Properties        MAGIC ITEM         <br>
Type, Slot        Armor, Feet        <br>
Armor Class        5        <br>
Boosts        +9 WIS, +9 INT        <br>
Effect        None        <br>
Weight &amp; Size        WT: 2.5 Size: ?        <br>
Class        ALL        <br>
Race        HUM, BAR, ERU, ELF, HIE, DEF, HEF, DWF, GNM, HFL, TRL, OGR        <br>
Obtained From        Efreeti Lord Djarn (L50)        <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
According to some posts on EQ Maps, the Efreeti Lord is a level 50 wizard, and his placeholder pops every 23 1/2 minutes. <br>
<br>
From my experience, breaking into the Efreeti Room takes more firepower than just holding it. So when we do go for some Eboots, we will need a commitment from at least a dozen people to show up for half an hour or so to get into the room, and then a single group can probably hold it for the evening.<br>
<br>
Because of the training/pathing/lava issues in this area, this is one of those times where it is absolutely vital to pay attention to the raid leader and keep guildchat to a minimum. (Once you are safely in the room, it's no big deal, just the breaking in part that is hectic.) <br>
<br>
To get to the Efreeti Lord's lair, zone into Sol B through the enterance in Lavastorm. Keep to the right through an intersection of tunnels and you will be near a lava lake with rock wall with a window in it. If you hear people telling you to meet up by the window room, this is probably what they are talking about. You will probably have to kill some kobolds here.<br>
<br>
Once the kobolds are wiped out, buff up and if possible get everybody going with DMF or Levitate. If nobody is there to cast these spells, you will have to swim through the lava. Hmmm... lavadipping...<br>
<br>
Head straight across the lava pool. The way will narrow into a tunnel, and you will come out on a little rock landing on the left. Here you will probably need to kill a bunch of bats and bugs and imps. These can swarm, so adjust your strategies for trainable dungeon fighting.<br>
<br>
Once you clear that, your puller (somebody with a lot of hit points) needs to head off to the right. There is a lava pool with some little stepping stones, and beyond it there is a smooth stone ramp. There are imps hanging out here, and they are grumpy and agro easily. Have your puller clear out the ones that are near the ramp, then move the whole party to the ramp.<br>
<br>
Here, it's important for everybody to hug the wall on the left, as you enter the ramp. Beyond this point there are imps and elementals, and they can train like crazy, and agro if you go too far up the ramp. The puller needs to grab all that stuff, one at a time, and bring it back to the group. The ramp, and the corridor above it, which circles a big lava pit, needs to be clear. This might take a while.<br>
<br>
Once this is clear, everybody hang a right and head up the ramp to the top. You will be on a pathway that rings a lava pit. The Efreeti Lord's room is either the first or second right(?). The way in is a curvy passage. I think there are usually two imps with the Efreeti Lord, plus a few just outside the room, so you are looking at breaking a spawn of 5 to 6 unhappy imps, and if the Lord is up, you also have to deal with him. <br>
<br>
Once the room is cleared, somebody needs to keep an eye on the time. The PH cycle is 24 minutes. Not sure about the random bodyguard imps. You can pull from the surrounding passages now. The imps are pretty good experience.<br>
<br>
Other things to keep an eye out for: Lots of rogue poison components drop here. Anything that looks like a leaf, a mushroom, or a root, give to your friendly neighborhood backstabber. Not sure what other incidentals drop along the way; I've seen words and runes drop here from time to time.<br>
<br>
<br>
If I missed something or got something wrong, please post a correction. I've only been on 3 Eboot runs, so there is probably some stuff I didn't remember correctly. <p><CENTER><HR WIDTH=250><FONT COLOR="RED" FACE="ARIAL"><B><I>Cute little cup-cake, baked by the devil!</I></B></FONT><BR>
